3. **`writeCentralFileHeader(ZipArchiveEntry ze)`** - Similar to the local file header, if the central file header is incorrect, it could lead to issues when reading the ZIP file.

5. **`deflate()`** - This method handles the compression of data. If the data is not compressed correctly, it could lead to issues when decompressing the file.
6. **`setEncoding(String encoding)`** - This method sets the encoding for the ZIP file. If the encoding is not set correctly, it could lead to issues with character representation.
